children.name: Get
children.helpText: Returns the string, which is handy for use with a special action, such as show.

children.name: To
children.helpText: Returns the string, which is handy for use with a special action, such as set.

children.name: Add Dynamic Variables From Unicode File
children.helpText: Load the given property file, respecting unicode, and set dynamic variables from the properties (but it is usually better to set them on a page).

children.name: Set Variables
children.helpText: Set several dynamic variables (optionally with comment) at once in a storytest.

children.name: Select Randomly
children.helpText: Randomly select one of the values in the rows of the rest of the table.

children.name: Get Symbol Named
children.helpText: Get the value of the Fit variable, so it can be used with a FitLibrary table.

children.name: Set Fit Variable
children.helpText: Set the Fit variable to the value, so a value from FitLibrary can be used in a Fit table.

children.name: Set System Property To
children.helpText: Set the Java system property, and the dynamic variable of the same name, to the value. Can be used to affect an application that is still be created.

children.name: Harvest Using Pattern From
children.helpText: Uses the regular expression to extract out one or more dynamic variables from the text, which is handy when text needs to be pulled apart to get at the required data.

children.name: Add Dynamic Variables From File
children.helpText: Load the given property file and set dynamic variables from the properties (but it is usually better to set them on a page).

children.name: Log
children.helpText: Logs the result of the action to the current (old-style) log file, if any.

children.name: Start Logging
children.helpText: Starts an obscure logging process to the file (this needs a better explanation).

children.name: Log Message
children.helpText: Log the message to an obscure logging process (this needs a better explanation).

children.name: Log Text
children.helpText: Log the message to the log4j log.

children.name: With Log 4 j
children.helpText: Starts a table for configuring log4j.

children.name: Logged
children.helpText: Logs the result of the action to log4j.

children.name: With Fixturing Logger
children.helpText: Starts a table for accessing the Fixturing-specific logger.

children.name: With Fit Library Logger
children.helpText: Starts a table for accessing the FitLibrary-specific logger.

children.name: File
children.helpText: Access the given file and allow actions on it in the rest of the table.

children.name: Record To File
children.helpText: Writes the dynamic variables to the file (this needs a better explanation).

children.name: Relative File
children.helpText: Access the given file and allow actions on it in the rest of the table.

children.name: Property File
children.helpText: Access the given property file and allow actions on it in the rest of the table.

children.name: Relative Property File
children.helpText: Access the given property file and allow actions on it in the rest of the table.

children.name: Help
children.helpText: Show all the actions in scope after the current table.

children.name: Help With
children.helpText: Show all the actions in scope that contain the string after the current table.

children.name: Help Keywords
children.helpText: Show all the actions in scope after the current table. This has been extended by netcare.

children.name: Help Defined Actions
children.helpText: Same as |help defined actions| but with the possibility to shorten the page names by this prefix.

children.name: Help Defined Actions
children.helpText: Shows a table of all defined actions that are available with its parameters, author and note. |define actions at|...| must be used before.

children.name: Loop
children.helpText: Treats the rest of a table as a while loop.

children.name: Loop Csv
children.helpText: Uses the rest of the table to setup and loop a CSV file.

children.name: Read Csv
children.helpText: Uses the rest of the table to read values and use them as dynamic variables from a CSV file.

children.name: For Each In
children.helpText: Iterates the following row with action over comma-separated values. See more

children.name: Loop With Timeout
children.helpText: Treats the rest of a table as a while loop. Will automatically stop when timeout has been reached. The timeout has to be given in milliseconds.

children.name: For Each Between And
children.helpText: Iterates the following row with action over index start to end. See more

children.name: Test Results
children.helpText: Returns the test results. Are the test results at the place used. Can be used in checks or variables.

children.name: Select
children.helpText: Select the named object so that it's actions take priority over others.

children.name: Abandon Storytest
children.helpText: Stop running the storytest immediately, so you can effectively ignore the rest of a storytest while exploring a problem.

children.name: Sleep For
children.helpText: Sleep for the given time in millseconds (the becomes special action may be better).

children.name: Continue Storytest
children.helpText: Continues test if it was abandoned before. This is useful at the beginning of a TearDown.

children.name: Also Run
children.helpText: The object that results from the action is added to the scope, so actions can be called on it in future.

children.name: Inform On Fail Or Error In Storytest
children.helpText:
The action must return an object that implements OnError.
Once there are fails or errors in a storytest, the method stopOnError() is called with the counts after each action.
children.syntax: |inform on fail or error in storytest|%1|

children.name: Note
children.helpText: Add text to defined actions to show it in |help defined actions|.

children.name: Deprecated
children.helpText: Add deprecated to defined actions to strike them through in the |''help defined actions''|.

children.name: Author
children.helpText: Add authors to defined actions to show it in |help defined actions|.

children.name: Set Stop On Error
children.helpText: Alter whether or not a storytest will stop on error, to avoid the extra time and errors.

children.name: Timeout
children.helpText: What is the timeout period (in ms) for the named timeout?

children.name: Timeout
children.helpText: Change the timeout period (in ms) for the named timeout.

children.name: Becomes Timeout
children.helpText: Change the timeout period (in ms) for becomes.

children.name: Becomes Timeout
children.helpText: What is the timeout period (in ms) for becomes?

children.name: Define Actions At
children.helpText: Load the defined actions from the given page and any sub-pages.

children.name: Set Expand Defined Actions
children.helpText: If set to true, expand calls to defined actions regardless.

children.name: Define Actions At From
children.helpText: Load the defined actions from the given page and any sub-pages, taking account of the folder location.

children.name: Runtime Configuration
children.helpText: Starts a table for changing configuation of FitLibrary. See more under "Actions for class GlobalActionScope"

children.name: Show
children.helpText: Show the value of the action is a cell added to the row.

children.name: Show
children.helpText: Show the result of the action in a cell added to the row.

children.name: Show As After Table
children.helpText: Show the message in a titled area that's added after the table.

children.name: Show Escaped
children.helpText: Show the value of the action in a cell added to the row. But the text is escaped so that any tags, etc will be visible.

children.name: Show With Tags
children.helpText: Show the value of the action in a cell added to the row. The tags will be visible.

children.name: Show Predefined
children.helpText: Show the value of the action is a cell added to the row. The text retains its layout across lines.

children.name: Show After
children.helpText: Show the value of the action in a folding area added after the table.

children.name: Show After As
children.helpText: Show the value of the action in a titled folding area added after the table.

children.name: Start Stop Watch
children.helpText: Start the stopwatch, so it can be used to fail a storytest if things take too long (with |stop stop watch|).

children.name: Stop Watch
children.helpText: Stop the stopwatch, and return how long it has been going (in ms), so you can cause the storytest to fail if it's been too long.

children.name: Record Variable With Value In Cleared Page
children.helpText: Defines variable with value in the given page. Clears the page contents before.

children.name: Record In Page
children.helpText: Saves value in the given page. The variable definition gets appended to the page contents.

children.name: Record In Cleared Page
children.helpText: Saves value in the given page. Clears the page contents before.

children.name: Record Variable With Value In Page
children.helpText: Defines variable with value in the given page. The variable definition gets appended to the page contents.

children.name: Not
children.helpText: Passes if the action fails or gives an error. Fails otherwise. Use notTrue if errors should be shown.

children.name: Reject
children.helpText: Passes if the action fails or gives an error. Fails otherwise. Use notTrue if errors should be shown.

children.name: Not True
children.helpText: Passes if the action fails and vice versa. Any errors are shown.

children.name: Slack
children.helpText: Sends a Slack message via the configured WebHooks.

children.name: As String
children.helpText: The object that results from the action can now be tested as a String.

children.name: Random Between And
children.helpText: Returns a random number beween min and max. Can be used to select a random xpath for example.

children.name: Known Issue
children.helpText: The rest of a table will be treated as known issues and marked as warnings instead of fails

children.name: Condition
children.helpText: Treats the rest of a table as condition.

children.name: Ignore
children.helpText: Place this in the first row of a table that is to be ignored (not run at all).

children.name: Comment
children.helpText: Place this in the first row of a table that is to be ignored (not run at all).

children.name: Define Action
children.helpText: Define a new action of that name and as given by the rest of the table.

children.name: Xref
children.helpText: Produce a cross reference of all the defined actions in the selected suite
children.syntax: |''xref''|page name of a defined action suite|

children.name: Auto Translate Defined Action Parameters
children.helpText: Allow for old-style use of parameters in defined actions, with no @{}.

children.name: Ignored
children.helpText: Place this in the first row of a table that is to be ignored (not run at all). The table is coloured to show it has been ignored.

children.name: Ignore Table
children.helpText: Place this in the first row of a table that is to be ignored (not run at all).

children.name: Set Variables With Comment
children.helpText: Set several dynamic variables (optionally with comment) at once in a storytest.

children.name: With Web Server For Testing
children.helpText: Run a web server to support testing.

children.name: With Web Services Client
children.helpText: Test a web service.

children.name: With Mock Web Services
children.helpText: Mock one or more web services.

children.name: With Proxy Server For Testing
children.helpText: Run a proxy server to support testing.

children.name: With Recording Web Services
children.helpText: Record the activity of a web services.

children.name: With Spider
children.helpText: Test a web application through one of several browsers.

children.name: With Kafka
children.helpText: Testing with Kafka

children.name: With Template
children.helpText: Use a template to create a file.

children.name: With Shell
children.helpText: Test an application through the command line.

children.name: With Rest
children.helpText: Test REST interfaces.

children.name: With PDF
children.helpText: Test the contents of a PDF

children.name: With Email
children.helpText: Test email.

children.name: With Xml
children.helpText: Test some xml.

children.name: With Date
children.helpText: Create some dates to use in the storytest, through actions that follow in the table.

children.name: Check
children.helpText: Check if the result of the action is the expected value.

children.name: Set
children.helpText: Set the dynamic variable to the result of the action (or the expression when the action starts with |=|).

children.name: Constraint
children.helpText: Treat the rest of the table as a constraint table.

children.name: Is
children.helpText: Check if the result of the action is the expected value.

children.name: Add Dynamic Variables From Unicode File
Note
children.helpText: Ignore the rest of the row.

children.name: Add Global
children.helpText: Take the result of the action (or an instance of the class) and add it as a new global to the scope.

children.name: Calculate
children.helpText: Treat the rest of the table as a calculate table.

children.name: Becomes
children.helpText: Check if the result of the action eventually becomes the expected value. It fails after the timeout period otherwise.

children.name: Show Dot
children.helpText: Treat the result of the action as a Dot specification, use Dot to create an image, and include it in the report.

children.name: Is Not
children.helpText: Check if the result of the action is not the unexpected value.

children.name: Add Named
children.helpText: Take the result of the action (or an instance of the class) and add it the current scope, with the given name. This is one way of allowing several objects to be used in a storytest at the same time.

children.name: Set Symbol Named
children.helpText: Set the Fit symbol to the result of the action.

children.name: Failing Constraint
children.helpText: Treat the rest of the table as a failing constraint table.

specialKeywords.name: Matches
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it matches the regular expression.

specialKeywords.name: Contains
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it contains the expected value.

specialKeywords.name: Less Than Equals
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it is less than or equal to the expected value.

specialKeywords.name: Greater Than
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it is greater than the expected value.

specialKeywords.name: Does Not Contain
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it does not contain the unexpected value.

specialKeywords.name: Less Than
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it is less than the expected value.

specialKeywords.name: Also Run As
specialKeywords.helpText: The object that results from the action is added to the scope, so actions can be called on it in future and it can be selected by name.

specialKeywords.name: Does Not Match
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it does not match the regular expression.

specialKeywords.name: Contains Ignore Case
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it contains the expected value (case insensitive).

specialKeywords.name: Greater Than Equals
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it is greater than or equal to the expected value.

specialKeywords.name: Eventually Contains
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it eventually contains the expected value. It fails if the timeout period for becomes is exceeded.

specialKeywords.name: Eventually Matches
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it eventually matches the regular expression. It fails if the timeout period for becomes is exceeded.

specialKeywords.name: Eventually Becomes
specialKeywords.helpText: Take the result of the action and see whether it eventually becomes the expected value. It fails if the timeout period for becomes is exceeded.

children.name: search result contact person at index

children.helpText: Search Result: Check if contact person at specific index contains person name. - E.g. use to check the order of displayed contact persons
